OL,3,CMan fighting insurance company two
OL,4,Cyears on from contracting dengue fever
OL,6,F"After unfortunately falling ill, the
OL,7,Fcustomer arranged for a private
OL,8,Fambulance company and made an up-front
OL,9,Fpartial payment of $1,000. This
OL,10,Finvolved the customer having to sign
OL,11,Fan agreement that he would be
OL,12,Fpersonally liable for any remaining
OL,13,Fcosts.
OL,15,F"We sympathise with Mr Soares'
OL,16,Fsituation and accept that we could
OL,17,Fhave been more proactive in our
OL,18,Fcommunication with him.
